        <td bgColor="black"><textarea cols="70" name="Message" rows="12" wrap="VIRTUAL">[quote]
I "care" about it because it does the game good in general. Even though if it [i]doesn't[/i] affect me directly.

And, it'll make playing the alts easier. If I ever care to play the alts...

This whole situation just goes to show that folks will complain about something no matter how good it is for others, for the sole reason that it bruises their ego. Your ego isn't that important - in fact, it's down right insignifacent.

I don't see where it stacks up to reason that "newbies" will be in their 50's and ruining raids. Even without the hell levels, one has already played quite a bit upon reaching their 50's and should have an understanding of what they're doing.

Those who do not simply would never have to begin with, and regardless of how long it took them to reach their post 50's, they would have still been making stupid mistakes.

Besides, hell levels have never bothered me much to begin with. The first one I "noticed" was 45, and that one didn't affect me much at all. 35 I actually forgot I was in one. Soloing certainly has its up sides, and many others where simply PL'ed through.

So when it comes right down to it, I don't think the argument has any base. Considering how much [i]good[/i] it does, it comes straight down to ego (and arrogance) and your argument is moot.

It's the way I see it. Somebody here may have a logical argument to counter mine, in which case I'd be interested in hearing it, but otherwise folks need to get over it.

The more good, the better. An obvious statement that pretty much carries itself, but one I think some folks need to ponder over.

~Mysk

